8. Editorial Review

Ñāṇavīra should be used as the severity engine of the Buddhist companion volume.

He prevents three common corruptions:

Turning Dhamma into metaphysical speculation.
Treating dependent arising as a merely historical/cosmological chain.
Talking about “de-rendering” while secretly preserving a self who owns the process.

He is difficult, sometimes brittle, and not always the best first teacher. But as a structural critic, he is indispensable.

