8. Editorial Review

This source is essential because it explains why the world feels so solid.

The Imaginarium model says ordinary consciousness is a conditioned rendering regime. Concept and Reality gives the Buddhist version of that mechanism: perception marks, language names, concepts proliferate, craving appropriates, and the self-world appears obvious.

This is the bridge between Dhamma and the project’s “rendering” language.

The key editorial warning: do not turn papañca into “thinking too much” in a shallow self-help sense. Papañca is deeper: it is the conceptual-affective expansion of experience around self-reference.

