8. Editorial Review

This source is the mechanical heart of the Buddhist blueprint.

For Path of Re-Rendering, it gives the cleanest Dhamma model of how the rendered world maintains itself:

ignorance → fabrication → consciousness → name-and-form → contact → feeling → craving → clinging → becoming → birth → suffering.

The crucial editorial move is not to treat this as a dead twelve-link chart. It should be read dynamically: a living loop by which experience becomes world, world becomes desirable/threatening, desire becomes appropriation, and appropriation becomes identity.

