8. Editorial Review

Nāgārjuna is indispensable because he protects the project from its most tempting mistake: turning “rendering” into a new essence.

The clean Imaginarium formulation:

The world is rendered, but rendering is empty.
The self is constructed, but construction is empty.
Nibbāna is release, but release is not a metaphysical object.

This source should be handled with precision. Do not make it nihilistic. Nāgārjuna is not saying nothing exists or nothing matters. He is saying things function precisely because they are dependently arisen and empty of intrinsic self-ground.

