8. Editorial Review

This source is invaluable but dangerous if mishandled.

Its strength is structure: it gives the entire path a technical grammar. Its weakness, for Imaginarium, is that its taxonomies can become too solid. So the best editorial stance is:

Use the map intensely, but do not reify the map.

The Visuddhimagga gives architecture; Ñāṇavīra and Nāgārjuna prevent architecture from becoming metaphysics; Ñāṇananda returns the map to lived cessation.

